{
  "texts": [
    "Each hidden layer implements a transformation of the output from the previous layer through a typically non-linear learnable function; the non-linearity of such transformations is key to their ability to learn complex input-output functions.",
    "Restricted Boltzmann Machine (RBM): generative ML model whose architecture consists of an input layer connected to only one hidden layer, see for example Fig. 4d.",
    "This architecture parametrizes a probability distribution over the input data and the hidden units (from which the probability of the data can be retrieved by marginalization over the hidden units).",
    "The hidden layer is useful for increasing the model's expressive power and for dimensionality reduction, see for example Fig. 2b.",
    "Deep learning: ML methods relying on neural network architectures with multiple hidden layers."
  ]
}